theorem interior_closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP1
  -- `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h₁ : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  -- `closure A` is contained in `closure (interior A)` thanks to `P1`.
  have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    apply closure_mono
    exact hP1
  -- Combine the two inclusions.
  exact Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂
